03/12/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- President Boris Tadic said on Wednesday (December 2nd) he is dissatisfied with the work of some cabinet ministers, but refused to name names. Tadic said this public warning is a chance for them to improve.
Meanwhile, a survey by Gallup suggests the public is also generally dissatisfied with the government's work. About 44% of respondents gave it a poor mark; 16% think it is performing well; 32% evaluated its work as satisfactory, 1% said it was excellent, while the rest described it as very poor. The survey was conducted in September. (RTS, Beta, Tanjug, SEEbiz - 02/12/09)
